-- Lakers Guard Steve Blake Fined $25,000 for Verbally Abusing Fan
-- B y   M a s o n   L e v i n s o n
-- 2012-11-06T18:59:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-06/lakers-guard-steve-blake-fined-25-000-for-verbally-abusing-fan.html
Los Angeles Lakers guard Steve Blake
was fined $25,000 by the National Basketball Association for
directing inappropriate language toward a fan after fouling out
late in a Nov. 2 loss to the Los Angeles Clippers.  The infraction occurred with 29.2 seconds left in a 105-95
defeat at Staples Center that dropped the Lakersâ€™ season record
to 0-3, the league said in a news release.  Blake, 32, was starting for injured point guard  Steve Nash .
He shot 2-of-6 for eight points, with two assists and three
turnovers in the loss.  To contact the reporter on this story:
